chapter 12, that she would be happy=\r\n=C2=A0if one does this with or without knowledge. Could you please comment =\r\non that. My understanding/interpretation could be wrong.\n=C2=A0\n2. I heard =\r\nfrom one of the pundits that since Gayatri Mantra is considered the greates=\r\nt of all mantras, one who has initiation in Gayatri Mantra (which is given =\r\nas part of upanayanam) need not have any other initiation.=C2=A0You could g=\r\nive your valuable opinion on the same. \n=C2=A0\nRegards,\n=C2=A0\nNagraj =C2=\r\n=A0\n\n--- On Tue, 10/26/10, Dr Satya Prakash &lt;backtocosmicroots@...=\r\n&gt; wrote:\n\n\nFrom: Dr Satya Prakash &lt;backtocosmicroots@...&gt;\nSubject:=\r\n [vedic-wisdom] Re: Translations, Initiation, Vedic vs Tantrik\nTo: vedic-wi=\r\nsdom@yahoogroups.com\nDate: Tuesday, October 26, 2010, 10:07 PM\n\n\n=C2=A0 \n\n\n=\r\n\n\n\nNamaste friends,\n\nEssentially I agree with Narasimha garu in most matter=\r\ns in this discussion. The only major point where I disagree is whether one =\r\ncan do Sri Sri Chandi path *without initiation*. The rest of the confusion =\r\non translation of mantras needs some clarification as there seems to be som=\r\ne unnecessary confusion. A few pointers:\n\n1. There are various sacred chant=\r\ns embedded within the Vedas, Puranas, Agamas etc. Broadly speaking such sac=\r\nred chants can be categorised as mantras, stotras, kavachas, dhyanams etc. =\r\nSome stotras too are also treated as mahamantras and mantras. The Samhita p=\r\nortion of the Vedas too is referred to as mantras.\n\n2. Undoubtedly mantras =\r\nand stotras have to be chanted in the original. Reading a translation is no=\r\nt even comparable to chanting the original chant. So far it is fine.\n\n3. Wh=\r\nilst mantra, stotra and kavacha are all based on Sabda/Vak, tradition makes=\r\n a distinction between them.\n\n4. As per the traditional view one doesn&#39;t ne=\r\ned to be initiated to chant a stotra or dhyanam. The case is not the same w=\r\nith most mantras. Mantras containing bijaksharas, agamic mantras, mantras o=\r\nf Mahavidyas etc need initiation. This is the traditional view. Mantras fro=\r\nm the Veda Samhita are not the same as these other mantras that need initia=\r\ntion, which are generally referred to as Agamic/Tantrik mantras. Whatever y=\r\nou call these mantras the actual idea is that these mantras are integral pa=\r\nrts of larger and distinct spiritual specialities that need initiation, as =\r\nin the case of Mahavidyas such as Kali or Sri.\n\n5. Vishnusahasranama, Sivas=\r\nahasranama, Aditya hrdayam etc do not need initiation as they fall under st=\r\notra category only. Lalitasahasranama and Devi Mahatmyam are traditionally =\r\nviewed not MERELY as stotras or parts of puranas. They have a larger status=\r\n as integral parts of a Mahavidya sadhana. Chanting them without initiation=\r\n is not recommended especially when the reader combines the navarna or shod=\r\nashi mantras too as an integral part of the chanting.\n\n6. I know from perso=\r\nnal interaction that acharyas belonging to both Kanchi as well as Sringeri =\r\nparamparas recommend initiation for both the sadhanas of Sri Sri Chandi and=\r\n Sri Vidya along with their respective NAVAKSHARI AND SHODASAKSHARI mantras=\r\n which are treated as an INTEGRAL LIMB (ANGA) of the sadhana. Acharyas of b=\r\noth these traditions hold that one needs to be initiated to chant the Navar=\r\nna as well as shodashakshari mantras.\n\n7. Recapping my earlier stance, Devi=\r\n Mahatmyam is a great text that has an independent status by itself as part=\r\n of a Mahavidya. It is simultaneously a Mahavidya, a Yogasastra as well as =\r\nan Advaitic text in the spirit of the Upanishads. ***As a Mahavidya the Nav=\r\nakshari is an integral part of Sri Sri Chandi path***. Thus tradition holds=\r\n that one needs to be initiated to chant it. However if one wishes to benef=\r\nit from the Yoga-Vedanta or Sacred myth aspects of the Devi Mahatmyam, , re=\r\nading the sacred myth in the vernacular has been recommended in my write-up=\r\n, as chanting the original along with the navakshari amounts to practicing =\r\nthe sadhana of a Mahavidya. In that case it is recommended to be initiated =\r\nand go through the specialised sadhanas properly under guidance.\n\n8. Arguab=\r\nly if an uninitiated person reads the Devi Mahatmyam in the original Sanskr=\r\nit as part of the *Pauranik* approach and not as a Mahavidya, it has an inh=\r\nerent problem in our times. The problem with attempting to do a parayana of=\r\n Devi Mahatmyam from texts alone (without initiation) is that most readers =\r\ninadvertently end up also chanting the Navarna mantra or stotras such as th=\r\ne Siddhakunjika stotram which too contain the bijaksharas.\n\n9. I you carefu=\r\nlly peruse my write-up on the Devi Mahatmyam, forget translating, nowhere d=\r\no I put down the Navarna mantra even in writing. Neither have I attempted t=\r\no write a commentary on it. Translations of mantras do not have the power o=\r\nf the original mantra as Sabda or Vak. However it is recommended to know th=\r\ne essence or import (artha) of the mantra and its sadhana while chanting it=\r\n. Infact `artha&#39; is the import, the essence of `Vak&#39;, not a translation! \n\n=\r\n10. For those who are already doing Sri Sri Chandi path without initiation,=\r\n there is no need to worry or be confused. There has to be a certain level =\r\nof samskara to be attracted to Sri Sri Chandi path itself. We all have it. =\r\nOtherwise we would not be doing it (initiation or no initiation). Please ke=\r\nep doing whatever you are doing. Just be cautious not to do sakama sadhana.=\r\n As Narasimha garu has rightly pointed out it is better to just do the sadh=\r\nana WITHOUT asking for any favours or results. That attitude itself will re=\r\nduce a lot of the potential problem. Things will happen on their own accord=\r\n in the natural flow. Leave the rest to the compassionate Goddess. \n\nHope t=\r\nhe above pointers help in clearing any confusion. \n\nRegards,\nSatya Prakash =\r\n\n\n=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=\r\n=3D=3D=3D\n\n--- In vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com, h ramalingam &lt;hramalingam@.=\r\n..&gt; wrote:\n&gt;\n&gt; Namaste everybody\n&gt; I want to share one anecdote happened in=\r\n front of Kanchi Maha Sannidanam Sri\n&gt; Sri Chandrasekara Bharathi Swamigal\n=\r\n&gt; When Swamigal was staying in a camp near Mysore in Karnataka One day all =\r\nthe\n&gt; learned persons male and female alike\n&gt; requested Swamigal to transla=\r\nte Sri Vishnu SahasraNamam in kannada language\n&gt; so that they can chant kno=\r\nwing the meaning fully.\n&gt; Swamigal didn&#39;t reply to this request which was m=\r\nade early in the morning.\n&gt; Later in the day after the days pooja etc were =\r\nover as usual Postman came to\n&gt; camp to deliver the posts came to Kanchi Mu=\r\ntt Swamigal. Swamigal was\n&gt; seriously looking at the cover\n&gt; in front of th=\r\ne learned members and was looking at one line written as PIN\n&gt; Code and fol=\r\nlowed by six numbers. Then he asked the learned members to\n&gt; explain the me=\r\naning of PIN Code and no one could tell that. But everyone\n&gt; understood the=\r\n significance of that number. Then swamigal asked his crew\n&gt; member to pick=\r\n up one LIFCO&#39;s abbreviations book from his library and read\n&gt; the meaning =\r\nas POSTAL INDEX NUMBER and told the group that even the meaning\n&gt; of PINCod=\r\ne was not known to the group and still it serves the purpose and\n&gt; people a=\r\nre using it in day to day work. Similarly not knowing the meaning of\n&gt; Vish=\r\nnu Saharanamam will not take away the benefits of chanting the stothsram\n&gt; =\r\nwas he told the group. Hope the above incidence bring some clue to our\n&gt; di=\r\nscussion forum\n&gt; RamanaPatham\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; On Tue, Oct 26, 2010 at 9:10 PM, N=\r\narasimha PVR Rao 