s. Mantra=\r\ns containing bijaksharas, agamic mantras, mantras of Mahavidyas etc need in=\r\nitiation. This is the traditional view. Mantras from the Veda Samhita are n=\r\not the same as these other mantras that need initiation, which are generall=\r\ny referred to as Agamic/Tantrik mantras. Whatever you call these mantras th=\r\ne actual idea is that these mantras are integral parts of larger and distin=\r\nct spiritual specialities that need initiation, as in the case of Mahavidya=\r\ns such as Kali or Sri.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;5. Vishnusahasranama, Sivasahasranama, Aditya=\r\n hrdayam etc do not need initiation as they fall under stotra category only=\r\n. Lalitasahasranama and Devi Mahatmyam are traditionally viewed not MERELY =\r\nas stotras or parts of puranas. They have a larger status as integral parts=\r\n of a Mahavidya sadhana. Chanting them without initiation is\n not recommend=\r\ned especially when the reader combines the navarna or shodashi mantras too =\r\nas an integral part of the chanting.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;6. I know from personal interac=\r\ntion that acharyas belonging to both Kanchi as well as Sringeri paramparas =\r\nrecommend initiation for both the sadhanas of Sri Sri Chandi and Sri Vidya =\r\nalong with their respective NAVAKSHARI AND SHODASAKSHARI mantras which are =\r\ntreated as an INTEGRAL LIMB (ANGA) of the sadhana. Acharyas of both these t=\r\nraditions hold that one needs to be initiated to chant the Navarna as well =\r\nas shodashakshari mantras.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;7. Recapping my earlier stance, Devi Maha=\r\ntmyam is a great text that has an independent status by itself as part of a=\r\n Mahavidya. It is simultaneously a Mahavidya, a Yogasastra as well as an Ad=\r\nvaitic text in the spirit of the Upanishads. ***As a Mahavidya the Navaksha=\r\nri is an integral part of Sri Sri Chandi path***. Thus tradition holds that=\r\n one needs to be initiated to chant it. However if one\n wishes to benefit f=\r\nrom the Yoga-Vedanta or Sacred myth aspects of the Devi Mahatmyam, , readin=\r\ng the sacred myth in the vernacular has been recommended in my write-up, as=\r\n chanting the original along with the navakshari amounts to practicing the =\r\nsadhana of a Mahavidya. In that case it is recommended to be initiated and =\r\ngo through the specialised sadhanas properly under guidance.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;8. Argu=\r\nably if an uninitiated person reads the Devi Mahatmyam in the original Sans=\r\nkrit as part of the *Pauranik* approach and not as a Mahavidya, it has an i=\r\nnherent problem in our times. The problem with attempting to do a parayana =\r\nof Devi Mahatmyam from texts alone (without initiation) is that most reader=\r\ns inadvertently end up also chanting the Navarna mantra or stotras such as =\r\nthe Siddhakunjika stotram which too contain the bijaksharas.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;9. I yo=\r\nu carefully peruse my write-up on the Devi Mahatmyam, forget translating, n=\r\nowhere do I put down the Navarna mantra even in\n writing. Neither have I at=\r\ntempted to write a commentary on it. Translations of mantras do not have th=\r\ne power of the original mantra as Sabda or Vak. However it is recommended t=\r\no know the essence or import (artha) of the mantra and its sadhana while ch=\r\nanting it. Infact `artha&#39; is the import, the essence of `Vak&#39;, not a transl=\r\nation! &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;10. For those who are already doing Sri Sri Chandi path with=\r\nout initiation, there is no need to worry or be confused. There has to be a=\r\n certain level of samskara to be attracted to Sri Sri Chandi path itself. W=\r\ne all have it. Otherwise we would not be doing it (initiation or no initiat=\r\nion). Please keep doing whatever you are doing. Just be cautious not to do =\r\nsakama sadhana. As Narasimha garu has rightly pointed out it is better to j=\r\nust do the sadhana WITHOUT asking for any favours or results. That attitude=\r\n itself will reduce a lot of the potential problem. Things will happen on t=\r\nheir own accord in the natural flow.\n Leave the rest to the compassionate G=\r\noddess. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Hope the above pointers help in clearing any confusion. &lt;BR=\r\n&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Regards,&lt;BR&gt;Satya Prakash &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=\r\n=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;--- In &lt;A href=3D&quot;http=\r\n://us.mc819.mail.yahoo.com/mc/compose?to=3Dvedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; =\r\nrel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups=\r\n.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/A&gt;, h ramalingam &lt;hramalingam@...&gt=\r\n; wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Namaste everybody&lt;BR&gt;&gt; I want to share one anec=\r\ndote happened in front of Kanchi Maha Sannidanam Sri&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Sri Chandrasek=\r\nara Bharathi Swamigal&lt;BR&gt;&gt; When Swamigal was staying in a camp near Myso=\r\nre in Karnataka One day all the&lt;BR&gt;&gt; learned persons male and female ali=\r\nke&lt;BR&gt;&gt; requested Swamigal to translate Sri Vishnu SahasraNamam in kanna=\r\nda language&lt;BR&gt;&gt; so that they can chant knowing the meaning fully.&lt;BR&gt;&g=\r\nt; Swamigal didn&#39;t reply to this request which was made early in the mornin=\r\ng.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Later in\n the day after the days pooja etc were over as usual Po=\r\nstman came to&lt;BR&gt;&gt; camp to deliver the posts came to Kanchi Mutt Swamiga=\r\nl. Swamigal was&lt;BR&gt;&gt; seriously looking at the cover&lt;BR&gt;&gt; in front of =\r\nthe learned members and was looking at one line written as PIN&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Code=\r\n and followed by six numbers. Then he asked the learned members to&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =\r\nexplain the meaning of PIN Code and no one could tell that. But everyone&lt;BR=\r\n&gt;&gt; understood the significance of that number. Then swamigal asked his c=\r\nrew&lt;BR&gt;&gt; member to pick up one LIFCO&#39;s abbreviations book from his libra=\r\nry and read&lt;BR&gt;&gt;